<subSubSection id="21C4BAC2C60D1B38FF6CFC67FE0DFBD3" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="6961E949C60D1B38FF6CFC67FE0DFBD3" blockId="11.[151,1436,689,1038]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis id="5BAA355BC60D1B38FF6CFC67FEBEFC84" bold="true" box="[199,315,833,857]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="AEDE92CAC60D1B38FEEFFC67FD83FC84" authorityName="Anker, Naderloo &amp; Marin" authorityYear="2010" box="[324,518,833,857]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Athanas" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iranicus">
<emphasis id="5BAA355BC60D1B38FEEFFC67FD83FC84" box="[324,518,833,857]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Athanas iranicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from a single male from 
<collectingCountry id="11C9A9D9C60D1B38FC74FC67FBABFC84" box="[991,1070,833,857]" name="Iran" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Qeshm</collectingCountry>
I. It is assigned to the 
<taxonomicName id="AEDE92CAC60D1B38FAEBFC67FE8AFCA0" authorityName="Ortmann" authorityYear="1894" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Athanas" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dimorphus">
<emphasis id="5BAA355BC60D1B38FAEBFC67FE8AFCA0" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Athanas dimorphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group, which is mainly characterized by the general shape of the first chelipeds and their ability to be carried flexed, with the chela fitting in the deeply depressed merus (
<bibRefCitation id="0D4F94B8C60D1B38FC79FCAFFB31FC7C" author="Anker, A. &amp; Jeng, M. S." box="[978,1204,905,930]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="454 - 472" refId="ref44817" refString="Anker, A. &amp; Jeng, M. S. (2007) Establishment of a new genus for Arete borradailei Coutiere, 1903 and Athanas verrucosus Banner and Banner, 1960, with redefinitions of Arete Stimpson, 1860 and Athanas Leach, 1814 (Crustacea: Decapoda: Alpheidae). Zoological Studies, 46, 454 - 472." type="journal article" year="2007">Anker &amp; Jeng 2007</bibRefCitation>
; Anker, 
<emphasis id="5BAA355BC60D1B38FABFFCACFAC0FC7C" box="[1300,1349,905,929]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">et al</emphasis>
. 2010). 
<taxonomicName id="AEDE92CAC60D1B38FF3CFC8BFED3FC18" authorityName="Anker, Naderloo &amp; Marin" authorityYear="2010" box="[151,342,941,965]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Athanas" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iranicus">
<emphasis id="5BAA355BC60D1B38FF3CFC8BFED3FC18" box="[151,342,941,965]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Athanas iranicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="AEDE92CAC60D1B38FDEBFC8BFC64FC18" authority="Hayashi, 2002" authorityName="Hayashi" authorityYear="2002" box="[576,993,941,965]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Athanas" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="squillophilus">
<emphasis id="5BAA355BC60D1B38FDEBFC8BFCB0FC18" box="[576,821,941,965]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Athanas squillophilus</emphasis>
Hayashi, 2002
</taxonomicName>
, described from 
<collectingCountry id="11C9A9D9C60D1B38FB35FC88FB64FC18" box="[1182,1249,942,965]" name="Japan" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Japan</collectingCountry>
, by the presence of dense rows of long setae on the palms of the chelipeds, a character that also distinguishes the species from the remaining congeners.
</paragraph>
